    description:
      "\u003cp\u003eRazorSecure is a highly disruptive cyber security SaaS provider that has invented a novel security technology initially for the transportation sector (rail, air, automotive), but with wide-reaching applications to protect critical infrastructure across global markets. We are a small team and our product delivery, reliability and scale exceeds our size. We do this with the best people, best tools and a culture of working together to solve complex problems. Will you be our next teammate to take on this challenge?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe are looking for two new teammates: a Frontend Developer and Full Stack Developer with DevOps Specialism.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWe need a Frontend Developer\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOur data-intensive dashboard, and accompanying visualisations, are the primary interface with our customers. They have to be reliable, fast and clearly communicate a broad range of security and operational information. Our legacy dashboard needs an overhaul and this is an opportunity to input a lot of creative direction into the tools and technology we should use.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf this is you, see below for details!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWe also need a Full Stack Developer (DevOps)\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDelivering high availability security services for critical infrastructure is hard. We have to automate many processes and use best-in-class operational tools. We do this with a DevOps culture across the entire team, but your role will focus on building and maintaining the supporting tools, automation, and processes.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf this is you, see below for details!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003ePractical Requirements for either job\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eLiving in the United Kingdom, ideally available to work from our office in Basingstoke. Working from other countries possible, via special arrangement.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMust be eligible to work in the UK\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAvailable for at least 4 days a week, preferably full-time.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eBenefits for either job\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eChallenging work in an interesting field with some awesome technology.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBeing part of a fast-growing company with an energetic and ambitious team.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eA culture focused on delivering high quality code while having fun\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCompetitive salary and share options.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePension and flexible holiday arrangements.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFrontend Developer job details\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe job involves:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDevelop and maintain a data-rich dashboard, with accompanying reports and visualisations.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eTranslating brief from design to clean, well-written code\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eBuild a comprehensive frontend testing suite both stubbed for unit testing and integrated for end-to-end testing.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCoach and support other team members in building new features with a frontend component.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eStay current with industry trends and source new ways for our business to improve.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eGet involved with full-stack end-to-end delivery of new features and bug fixes.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSupporting the agile development process including taking on rotating team roles, participating in planning and retrospectives.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIntegrate our software with partner systems and provide technical support to customers where needed.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMaintaining internal and external documentation associated with the product, and internal development activities.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe are looking for:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience developing and deploying data-rich frontend applications\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eEye for design and able to deliver an application from a base specification\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDeep knowledge of their weapon of choice (React/Vue/Angular/other...)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eGood working knowledge of Linux, git and the command-line\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCommitted to high engineering standards\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe cherry on the cake:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAttitude of continuous improvement.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCan design and communicate complex software architectures.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDeployed software agents to a range of hardware.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWorked in a security function.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eGoogle-fu.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFluency in another spoken language.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe tactical mastery of Iron Man.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe detective skills of Batman.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe situational awareness of Samus. (We'll hire you if you are Batman, or Iron Man, or Samus.)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eFull Stack Developer (DevOps) job details\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe job involves:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eImprove efficiency and effectiveness of development and operations.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMentor and support team members with DevOps tools and processes.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSpeed up delivery to production, while not impacting availability, security and performance.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eStay current with industry trends and source new ways for our business to improve.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eGet involved with full-stack end-to-end delivery of new features and bug fixes.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSupporting the agile development process including taking on rotating team roles, participating in planning and retrospectives.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIntegrate our software with partner systems and provide technical support to customers where needed.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMaintaining internal and external documentation associated with the product, and internal development activities.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe are looking for:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience developing and deploying complex, data-rich and distributed applications.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSupportive and creative attitude to solving team DevOps challenges.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAt least 1 year experience in developing in Python.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eGood working knowledge of Linux, git and the command-line.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFamiliarity with relational and NoSQL databases.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCommitted to high engineering standards.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe cherry on the cake:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eAttitude of continuous improvement.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCan design and communicate complex software architectures.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDeployed software agents to a range of hardware.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eWorked in a security function.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eGoogle-fu.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFluency in another spoken language.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe tactical mastery of Iron Man.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe detective skills of Batman.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eThe situational awareness of Samus. (We'll hire you if you are Batman, or Iron Man, or Samus.)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n",
